To calculate the Gross Profit Margin, we use the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{\text{Gross Profit}}{\text{Total Revenue}} \right) \times 100 \]

From the given problem:
- Gross Profit = 1,713,437.82
- Total Revenue = 3,025,437.82

Now, plug these values into the formula:

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = \left( \frac{1,713,437.82}{3,025,437.82} \right) \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 0.5663 \times 100 \]

\[ \text{Gross Profit Margin} = 56.63\% \]

So, the solution is:

```json
{"solution": {'Gross Profit Margin': '56.63%'} }
```
